#Text=Perform Preventative Home Maintenance
#Text=Maintaining that home is not something that most of us are prepared for and can sometimes be overwhelming .
#Text=However , if planned correctly , home maintenance can be a rewarding experience .
#Text=Home maintenance should be thought of like the maintenance of your car .
#Text=To keep it performing at its best , it should be done on time , correctly and by someone who knows what they ’re doing .
#Text=The secret to lower out of pocket expenses and lowering the number of unplanned breakdowns is a good preventative regime .
#Text=In the long run preventative home maintenance is much cheaper than reactive maintenance that you 're unprepared for .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Doing Monthly Home Maintenance
#Text=Check your water heater .
#Text=Check pressure and temperature valves are working and pressure in line with owner ’s manual guidance .
#Text=A local plumber can do a more thorough inspection from time to time and fix more complex issues .
#Text=Check your water filters .
#Text=Clean and wash these accordingly .
#Text=These like air filters vary depending on device model .
#Text=A qualified plumber can assist in inspecting or replacing filters as needed .
#Text=Unclog your drains .
#Text=Inspect , unclog and clean as required .
#Text=Checking for pests ( animal or plant ) to ensure no blockages .
#Text=A pest control professional can be called to assist if you do spot an issue .
#Text=Clean your garbage disposal .
#Text=Pass ice cubes through to clean blades .
#Text=You can also mix in small amounts of vinegar to help with cleansing .
#Text=Check your air filters .
#Text=Clean reusable filters as directed by supplier and replace non-usable filters .
#Text=Life expectancy of these air filters varies , so be sure to check what the frequency ought to be for your filter/device .
#Text=Clean filter means more efficient devices and a healthier home .
#Text=Keep your appliances in good shape .
#Text=Inspect and clean as required home appliances .
#Text=Replacing damaged parts as appropriate
#Text=Clean range top and burners
#Text=Deep clean laminate surfaces .
#Text=Deep clean surfaces using appropriate tools and chemicals
#Text=Clean your tiles .
#Text=Inspect and clean grouting .
#Text=Check your fire extinguisher .
#Text=Inspect pressure gauge to ensure reading is in line with manufacturer requirements .
#Text=Inspect nozzle is not blocked at tip .
#Text=Test your smoke detectors .
#Text=Test using push button , and replace batteries if device is not operating .
#Text=The entire device is usually changed out every 5 years .
#Text=Test your carbon monoxide detectors .
#Text=Test using push button , and replace batteries if device is not operating .
#Text=The entire device is usually changed out every 5 years .
#Text=Check your garage door .
#Text=Test auto-reverse safety feature is working as intended .
#Text=Check your electrical wiring .
#Text=It 's always advised to get a licensed electrician to perform inspection on electrical wiring .
#Text=For the obvious reason of safety , but also to ensure important issues are not missed and are caught by a trained person .
#Text=Always hire a qualified electrician to perform electrical work .
#Text=Do an exterior and interior walk through .
#Text=It 's good practice to do a walk around of the exterior and interior of your home .
#Text=Keeping an eye for anything that looks out of the ordinary .
#Text=Such as , exposed wiring , cracked wall , water pooling where it should n’t be , etc.
#Text=This will help you spot problem before they become major and costly .
#Text=Doing Annual Home Maintenance
#Text=Go through this spring home maintenance checklist :
#Text=Annual air conditioner ( A/C ) maintenance – a HVAC specialist should be called to perform the annual maintenance of you air conditioning system .
#Text=Servicing means better performance and small problems can be captured before they become major .
#Text=Refrigerator maintenance – a HVAC specialist performing the above task can also take care of this .
#Text=It includes cleaning of the condenser coils which collect dust and dirt .
#Text=This task should be performed every season or quarterly if you have pets or allergies .
#Text=Attic inspection – you want to look out for pests , leaks , rot and fungus .
#Text=The insulation should also be inspected for any abnormalities .
#Text=Landscaping – clear dead plants and trees and check trees and bushes have not grown to interfere with electrical wiring nor plumbing and pipes .
#Text=You may also get a landscaper to work on areas where a professional is required .
#Text=Follow through with this summer home maintenance checklist :
#Text=Heating system – during summer months its best to inspect and test your heating system .
#Text=As winter approaches , you would have had time to fix any issues ahead of time and save money by planning in advance .
#Text=Follow the owner ’s manual as each system differs .
#Text=Plumbing systems – inspection plumbing systems including faucets , shower heads and toilet flush for leaks .
#Text=Check water pressure in plumbing systems across the house .
#Text=For any major plumbing problems hire a professional to avoid further damage .
#Text=Fixing plumbing issues in the summer is better than frozen or burst piping in the winter .
#Text=Electrical systems – a simple check is turning off and on circuits .
#Text=A qualified electricianshould be the only person to perform further intrusive testing .
#Text=Pest control – check interior and exterior of your home for pests ( animal or plant ) .
#Text=A pest control specialist can provide you with varying solutions should the need arise .
#Text=Complete the autumn/fall home maintenance checklist :
#Text=Weather proofing – inspect the interior and exterior of your home to ensure weather proofing is intact .
#Text=This includes the caulking , the finishes and seals around windows and doors .
#Text=Most of these can be repaired with some DIY work , or you can hire a handyman to assist with the task .
#Text=Winter preparation – now is a good time to ensure you have sidewalk salt , snow snow shovels , etc. It ’s also a good idea to flush out outdoor water faucets to avoid bust pipes .
#Text=Chimney – clean out chimneys .
#Text=Gutters and roofing – clean out gutters and check roof for cracks and get them sealed .
#Text=Finish up the year with the winter home maintenance checklist :
#Text=Icicles – remove icicles from gutters and drainage systems to avoid breakages .
#Text=Snow – maintain good level of snow removal to avoid large build up .
#Text=Always take precautions and follow best practices when shoveling snow .
#Text=Basement – during winter is the best time to inspect interior of your home and the much-needed attention can now be focused on the basement ’s needs .
#Text=Plumbing – keep an eye out on your interior and exterior plumbing to avoid leaks and burst pipes .
